Arrange clams on a rack in a steamer or Dutch oven. Add 2 cups hot water, cover tightly and steam over medium heat 5 to 10 minutes, or just until shells open. Discard unopened clams. Heat olive oil in a nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and celery; sauté 6 to 8 minutes. Add garlic; sauté 2 to 3 minutes. Add tomatoes; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Add seasonings. Place clams in large soup} bowls. Spoon tomato sauce over clams. Sprinkle with parsley.